    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><certainty match="preceding-sibling::node()" locus="value"/> <lb n="2"/>Amatori patriae et civium suor<supplied reason="lost">um quod</supplied> ex indulgentia sacra <lb n="3"/>civibus suis feras dentatas quattuor vivas donavit <lb n="4"/>ex decreto splendidissimi ordinis bigam decrev<expan><ex>eru</ex><abbr>nt</abbr></expan> <lb n="5"/>Porfyri Porfyri
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): AE 1942/43 geht von einer nur vierzeiligen Inschrift aus; Lesung AE 1942/43 verbessert in AE 2010, 1780. Monument used three times: original text in tabula ansata erased; second text on a metal plaque removed; last IRT 603. Inschriftträger: tetrapylon shaped monument supporting a biga. Dekor: two ships carved in relief on the frontal pillars. Interpunktion: Palmette.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography">
                <listBibl><bibl>AE 1942/43, 0004. (B)</bibl><bibl>IRT 603.</bibl><bibl>I. Tantillo - F. Bigi (Hrsg.), Leptis Magna. Una città e le sue iscrizioni in epoca tardoromana (Cassino 2010) 408-412, Nr. 50; fig. 7.10 u. fig. 7.11; tav. 17; fig. 10.57 (Zeichnung). - AE 2010.</bibl><bibl>AE 2010, 1780.</bibl><bibl>S. Aurigemma, AI 7, 1940, 81-84; fig. 17 u. 18. - AE 1942/43.</bibl><bibl/></listBibl>
            </div>
